**Can you attach an example that shows the issue?  (Must be openly licensed, ideally in test_regress format.)**

```sv
typedef struct {int pc} state_t;

function int A(inout state_t state);
  state.pc++;
  return 1;
endfunction

function int B(inout state_t state);
  state.pc++;
  return 2;
endfunction

module test(input logic clk);
  int value = 0;
  state_t state;
  always @(posedge clk) begin
    if (condition) value = A(state);
    else begin
      value = B(state);
      // $display("difference");
    end
    // or
    value = condition ? A(state) : B(state);
  end
endmodule
```
The code above will increment pc twice regardless of the condition. However when I uncomment `$display("difference")`, it works fixes: increments pc once. I am not sure if the code snippet provided above will reproduce the bug. But the code in my repo does.

If statement: https://github.com/weisrc/nesv/blob/main/src/cpu/matrix/1.sv#L7
